28/06/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police on Wednesday (28 June) arrested two more suspects in connection with the May attack on the country's top administrative court, the Council of State, in which one judge was killed and four others injured. 
Authorities say the main suspect in the case, lawyer Alparslan Aslan, provided the names of the two. 
No other details were disclosed. 
(NTV - 28/06/06)
